{
  "texts": [
    "SPECK is an additionrotation-XOR-based algorithm that works on block sizes of 32, 48, 64, 96, and 128-bit and key sizes of 64,72,96,128,144,128,192, and 256-bit for 22, 22, 23, 26, 27, 28, 29, 32, 33, and 34, respectively.",
    "The family is susceptible to differential attack, linear differential attack, impossible differential attack, and multi-dimensional linear attack on SIMON.",
    "SPECK is defenceless against differential attacks and rectangle attacks [83].",
    "The authors also confirmed important differential trials on SIMON 34, 48, and 64-bit versions.",
    "Another notable discovery concerning SIMON demonstrates an efficient algorithm for calculating the differential probabilities (DP) of the modular AND operation with both independent inputs and rotationally dependent inputs."
  ]
}